<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-048-420  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 048 420.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Jan 15 1990 v10 n3 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>More big companies ink outsourcing pacts. (companies seekingoutside services to manage Management Information Systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>DePompa, Barbara.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Outsourcing is growing more popular as organizations downsize andreorganize their management information systems.andP;  As companiesbecome more competitive, MIS departments become candidates foroutsourcing as a way to cut costs.andP;  Third-party services arebroad, including data processing and management of communicationsand networks.andP;  Companies such as Andersen Consulting, EDS Corp,DEC and IBM offer outsourcing services.andP;  In August 1989, IBM wasawarded a contract from Eastman Kodak to manage its data center,and many Kodak MIS employees became IBM workers.andP;  Kodak and otherlarge companies making use of third-party management services willremain active in long-range strategic MIS planning and in theacquisition of new equipment in order to retain control over thecompany's data processing and communications infrastructure.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Third-Party MaintenanceMISCost ReductionInformation Resources ManagementManagement of EDPSupport Services.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>